&lt;h3&gt;Styles&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To see all the styles that this theme offers, please visit the &lt;a href=&quot;http://127.0.0.1/GetSimpleCMS-3.3.2/styles/&quot;&gt;Styles&lt;/a&gt; page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This theme includes support for the following elements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;blockquote&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pre&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;code&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ordered lists&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;unordered lists&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;definition lists&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;form&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This theme natively supports the following &lt;strong&gt;form &lt;/strong&gt;elements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;form&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fieldset&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;legend&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;input&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;textarea&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;option&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;label&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;select&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Second Sidebar&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The LCARS Theme supports a second sidebar to the right of the first sidebar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To activate it, follow these steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In your admin dashboard, click on the &quot;Theme&quot; tab.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Click on the &quot;Edit Components&quot; button on the right.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Click on the &quot;Add Component&quot; button.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the &quot;Title:&quot; box, enter &quot;Sidebar2&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;That&#039;s it! You&#039;re done! Simply enter the text you want to appear (in HTML) in the box.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For best appearances, try to keep headings in the sidebars to a single line. If necessary, break them into two lines:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&amp;lt;h2&amp;gt;This is a 2-&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;h2&amp;gt;line header&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Which would then look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; class=&quot;center&quot; src=&quot;http://127.0.0.1/GetSimpleCMS-3.3.2/data/uploads/images/lcars-2-line.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 213px; height: 125px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Additional Features&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The headings (h1, h2, h3, etc.) are smaller in the sidebars than they are in the main content area. See these demo pages for an example.&lt;/p&gt;
